1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Applause

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Beyond our solar system, there are planets that orbit other stars.

3
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:27,000
They are called exoplanets, exoplanets because they are outside the solar system.

4
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:02,200
As you can imagine,

5
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:06,960
It's really difficult to detect them because they are very far from us.

6
00:00:08,720 --> 00:00:09,760
Yet, regularly,

7
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:11,600
astronomers

8
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:14,360
they announce that they have discovered new exoplanets.

9
00:00:15,760 --> 00:00:17,760
There is even a recent study.

10
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:20,160
who suggests

11
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:23,800
that among all the exoplanets that must exist in our galaxy,

12
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:27,280
There could be 20 billion.

13
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:11,000
and thus to offer a potentially interesting environment for life. Do you realize, 20 billion?

14
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Well, if we want to study the criteria for a planet's habitability,

15
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:22,000
We will focus on four criteria that must be met for this study to be a success.

16
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:07,760
We will focus on four criteria that must be met for this study to be a success.

17
00:00:12,160 --> 00:00:14,360
The first criterion is that the planet is the right distance from the star.

18
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:18,520
So actually the image you see on the screen is a drawing of an exoplanet.

19
00:00:21,720 --> 00:00:22,240
because they are too far away, we cannot see this level of detail.

20
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:29,640
But what the artist intended to depict is a planet in the habitable zone of the star.

21
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
That is, the surface on which the temperature would be right for water to remain in a liquid state for a sufficient amount of time.

22
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Closer to us, within our solar system, there are also planets that can tell us about habitability.

23
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:03,240
So of course, today, to our knowledge,

24
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:07,000
There is only one that is habitable and inhabited.

